# MCP Tool Safety Standards

## Every tool must validate paths through PathGuard

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
export async function readFile(params: ReadFileParams): Promise<ToolResult> {
  const guard = new PathGuard(process.env.ALLOWED_DIRS?.split(",") ?? []);
  if (!guard.isAllowed(params.path)) {
    return { error: "Path not in allowed directories", code: "PATH_BLOCKED" };
  }
  // ... proceed
}

// ❌ BAD — no path validation
export async function readFile(params: ReadFileParams): Promise<ToolResult> {
  return fs.readFile(params.path, "utf-8");
}
```

## Destructive tools must use explicit intent params

Write, delete, and overwrite tools must require a `confirm: true` parameter so agents explicitly acknowledge the operation.

## All tools return structured errors

Never throw unhandled exceptions from a tool handler. Catch and return `{ error: string, code: string }`.

## Register every tool in TOOLS.md

If you add a tool to code but not to `TOOLS.md`, the tool is undiscoverable. Both must stay in sync.
